issues.description: In the Template Repository, the method singFarmSongVerse in Farm.java is declared without parameters due to a commented-out parameter (/*Animal animal*/), whereas the Problem Statement and Solution Repository expect it to have an Animal parameter. This mismatch would confuse students, as they might attempt to implement the method based on the problem description but find the template structure incompatible, leading to compilation errors and misunderstanding of the intended design.
issues.suggested_fix: Correct the template by updating the method signature in Farm.java to include the parameter, e.g., change 'private void singFarmSongVerse(/*Animal animal*/) {' to 'private void singFarmSongVerse(Animal animal) {', ensuring students can build upon the intended structure without initial conflicts.
